text: Essam Ismail (born 5 August 1967) is an archer from Egypt. He was born on 5 August 1967. He competed at the 2000 and the 2004 Summer Olympics.Essam SayedEssam Ismail, left, and May Mansour, of Egypt, take aim during Olympic familiarization practice in Panathinaiko Stadium in Athens, Saturday Aug. 14, 2004. Mansour, who was granted permission to wear the headcover, is matched against Korea's Park Sung Hyun, the world record holder, when competition begins Sunday.
